body:
WeÕre having a boy!! __
 

 I couldnÕt be more excited to share this news. From the beginning of my pregnancy we thought we wouldnÕt find out the gender until the baby arrived. I loved the idea of keeping it a surprise because thatÕs what our parents had done for us. But through this pregnancy it was so difficult at the beginning to think about pregnancy without thinking of how hard each day had been because of the sickness. We decided to find out the gender at 25 weeks and it brought us so much joy finding out we are having a little boy. Picturing him and what parenthood will look like has been the most exciting few months and we cannot wait to meet him 
 

 Beautiful earrings and baby wrap arounds by @abigail_maryann_clarke_

body:
GRWM for a date night with my husband, wearing my traditional Inuit clothing!_
 

 IÕm wearing my Atiqluk and matching @annabellecosmetics makeup. Our traditional Inuit clothing is such an important part of our culture. Everything we wear has such meaning and importance behind it. I love using makeup to tie it all together - bringing my culture into the way I present and express myself gives me so much pride and confidence. This is when I feel the most beautiful __
 

 #AnnabelleForEveryone #AnnabelleCosmetics #AnnabelleStaysOn #Ad

@canadagoose X @varcticfashion 
 

 Recognition is so important! Canada Goose is recognizing Inuit artists and Inuit communities through their Project Atigi collection which features the beautiful design work of Victoria Kakuktinniq. I am so grateful and proud to be apart of this.
